Title: Generic radio frequency data receiver
Maintainer: Jasper Scholte <NightNL@outlook.com>
Source: rtl_433-21.12.tar.gz
License: GPL-2.0-or-later
LicenseFiles: COPYING
Type: ipkg
Description:   rtl_433 (despite the name) is a generic data receiver, mainly for the 433.92 MHz, 868 MHz (SRD), 315 MHz, 345 MHz, and 915 MHz ISM bands.

  To use it with OpenWrt you need a Realtek RTL2832 based DVB USB dongle (SoapySDR is not supported).
https://github.com/merbanan/rtl_433
Jasper Scholte <NightNL@outlook.com>
@@

Package: rtl_433-ssl
Version: 21.12-0
Depends: +libc +USE_GLIBC:librt +USE_GLIBC:libpthread +librtlsdr +rtl-sdr +libtool-bin +libopenssl
Conflicts: 
Menu-Depends: 
Provides: 
Build-Variant: ssl
Section: utils
Category: Utilities
Repository: base
Title: Generic radio frequency data receiver (with SSL support)
Maintainer: Jasper Scholte <NightNL@outlook.com>
Source: rtl_433-21.12.tar.gz
License: GPL-2.0-or-later
LicenseFiles: COPYING
Type: ipkg
Description:     rtl_433 (despite the name) is a generic data receiver, mainly for the 433.92 MHz, 868 MHz (SRD), 315 MHz, 345 MHz, and 915 MHz ISM bands.

  To use it with OpenWrt you need a Realtek RTL2832 based DVB USB dongle (SoapySDR is not supported).

  This package includes OpenSSL support which allows you to send data to influxDB/MQTT using TLS.
https://github.com/merbanan/rtl_433
Jasper Scholte <NightNL@outlook.com>
@@


